Attack Type: This vulnerability enables remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on the affected system without requiring authentication. By exploiting the improper delimiter handling in the `preg_replace` function, an attacker can inject and execute malicious PHP code, potentially compromising the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the system.
Unauthorized access to sensitive information by bypassing access controls through crafted URI requests.
Path Traversal Attack, Remote Code Execution

This vulnerability allows for arbitrary remote code execution. An attacker can exploit this by sending malicious requests to the unsecured Gateway Actuator endpoint, leading to unauthorized command execution on the server.
This vulnerability enables unauthorized access to the system without authentication, allowing attackers to gain administrative privileges.
This vulnerability allows unauthorized access to web service endpoints, leading to potential unauthorized data exposure and manipulation.

The attack involves unauthorized access to sensitive information by exploiting the CLI command parser's misconfiguration, allowing attackers to read arbitrary files on the Jenkins controller file system.
